Receive information related to the project and distribute the information to the responsible parties;

Maintain a register of all project documents by regular updates of related logs to track all documents;

Manage and monitor timelines related to submissions or review process by email notification and reminders;

Perform operational performance and financial analysis, cost-benefit analysis, and econometric analysis;

Manage program and project document management system and retrieve project documentation communicated between related teams;

Interface with the project team on document control matters and train all applicable project staff in the use of the document management system;

Attend meetings, as required, take minutes, distribute minutes of meeting, follow-up on actions;

Coordinate project team monthly and bi-weekly progress meetings; draft, release agendas and minutes;

Report preparation and drafting of correspondence;

Ensure all project documentation is compliant with project formats, company standards, styles, and verification forms;

Communicate with clients, sub-consultants, and team members in a professional manner;

Review final reports and submissions for delivery and prepare courier packages;

Research best practices, assist with developing a business case, and prepare client presentations;

With the Director's guidance, prepare project plans including, work breakdown structures, scheduling, cost plan, quality plan, change management plan, communications plan, risk plan, procurement plan and resource plan;

Track and report on project plan progress for cost and schedule reporting, change control and analyzing areas with deviations from the project plan;

Monitor weekly performance and quality; recommend corrective actions to the Director;

Maintain and monitor project issue logs, and provide support to the other Managers as required;

Other duties as assigned/required.




